This species is only known from the original Colombian collection by Justin Goudot, who collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,290,727,752]" name="Colombia" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">Colombia</collectingCountry>
between 1822 and 1842 (
<bibRefCitation author="Cardiel, J. M." box="[581,788,727,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" refId="ref17299" refString="Cardiel, J. M. (1995 a) Acalypha (Euphorbiaceae). Flora de Colombia. Monografia nº 15. Universidad Nacional de Colombia y Real Jardin Botanico-CSIC, Madrid, 153 pp." type="book" year="1995">Cardiel 1995a: 10</bibRefCitation>
). The municipality of Muzo was overused for its emerald deposits and has been greatly deforested; thus, we do not rule out that the species could be extinct.
</paragraph>
